headline: EU antitrust regulators to decide on Mars' Kellanova deal by June 25
summary: BRUSSELS (Reuters) -European Union antitrust regulators will decide by June 25 whether to clear Mars' $36 billion takeover of Pringles maker Kellanova, according to a European Commission filing.  Family-owned candy giant Mars announced the deal in August last year that will bring together brands from M&M's and Snickers to Pringles and Pop-Tarts under one roof.  The U.S. packaged food sector is experiencing a wave of consolidation as companies seek scale to weather the impact of inflation-weary consumers cutting back and shifting their purchases to private label brands.
